        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1060383150" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6470405749962019368">This was something I picked up when &apos;in between books&apos; as I had read it before many years previously. Mauppasant like a lot of great artists trod a thin line between genius and madness. This is in the main a work of genius. Most of the stories subtly show the hypocrisy and unfairness of 19th century French society and champion the underdog.<br/><br/>Some stories are fairly light but all are worth reading. My favourites are Boule de Suif and An Idyll. The latter is five pages in which a wet nurse suckles a</span>
  <span id="freeText6470405749962019368" style="display:none">This was something I picked up when 'in between books' as I had read it before many years previously. Mauppasant like a lot of great artists trod a thin line between genius and madness. This is in the main a work of genius. Most of the stories subtly show the hypocrisy and unfairness of 19th century French society and champion the underdog.<br /><br />Some stories are fairly light but all are worth reading. My favourites are Boule de Suif and An Idyll. The latter is five pages in which a wet nurse suckles a starving labourer...a weird and beautiful tale.<br /><br />Maupassant apparently worked hard to perfect his art. He certainly managed it. Nice to read short stories for a change.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6470405749962019368" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


