        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2129373110" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11288676208143672884"><b> Guy de Maupassant </b> selected stories capture greed, self-interest and desire for power..<br/>Most of the characters reveal their true natures in an unusual situation and a moralistic analysis of society..<br/> <br/>Most of his stories portrays the strength and power of women as well the greed and dishonest in men..His women mainly pander to male appetites and domestic needs, with occasional hints of a more iconic role. <br/>Surprisingly, since he is considered a master of the short story and one of the earliest &quot;mo</span>
  <span id="freeText11288676208143672884" style="display:none"><b> Guy de Maupassant </b> selected stories capture greed, self-interest and desire for power..<br />Most of the characters reveal their true natures in an unusual situation and a moralistic analysis of society..<br /> <br />Most of his stories portrays the strength and power of women as well the greed and dishonest in men..His women mainly pander to male appetites and domestic needs, with occasional hints of a more iconic role. <br />Surprisingly, since he is considered a master of the short story and one of the earliest "modern" short story writers, I had never read any of Maupassant's stories before. The collection I read includes a varied selection, enough to give an idea of the breadth of his topics and to show Maupassant's ability to briefly but brilliantly depict places and people.. <br /><br />Seems, Maupassant love boats and the sea and as a result, a lot of his stories take place within this environment.</span>
