    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3382430988" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3382430988" />
    <a title="Carlmaria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/103121260-carlmaria"><img alt="Carlmaria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1587293908p2/103121260.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3382430988?book_show_action=true">Jun 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carlmaria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carlmaria" href="/user/show/103121260-carlmaria">Carlmaria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3382430988" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2360425268144935904">Boule de Suif, a French short story from 1880 which inspired Russian cinema in the Stalin years of great terror, then two years later a director who ultimately supported Nixon (John Ford directed Stagecoach where Boule de suif becomes the prostitute Dallas) and later a 1945 film about occupied France (Christian Jaque), for sure, such a story must touch on the universal. The character of the proletarian prostitute in front of the representatives of capitalism and morality behind the closed doors </span>
  <span id="freeText2360425268144935904" style="display:none">Boule de Suif, a French short story from 1880 which inspired Russian cinema in the Stalin years of great terror, then two years later a director who ultimately supported Nixon (John Ford directed Stagecoach where Boule de suif becomes the prostitute Dallas) and later a 1945 film about occupied France (Christian Jaque), for sure, such a story must touch on the universal. The character of the proletarian prostitute in front of the representatives of capitalism and morality behind the closed doors of a horse coach (and later a fateful inn) is as powerful a character as Gavroche or Quasimodo. I understand why Pixar would hesitate to produce the animation film and Rodgers and Hammerstein the Broadway musical. Yet provided they cast a young and voluptuous singer in the part, Boule de Suif would make a peerless musical.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2360425268144935904" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

