        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3514017201" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14625817141222214366">I am clearly in the minority concerning the stories of Guy De Maupassant. I am not overly impressed. He does capture individual personalities and peccadilloes accurately and the description of scenes and times is very good; but I thought the stories were too long by half and just not worth the effort. I suppose they were considered racy or ribald for the time, but not so much anymore. Most of them I found to be predictable and forgettable. I am glad I have read them. I have had this book for 30 </span>
  <span id="freeText14625817141222214366" style="display:none">I am clearly in the minority concerning the stories of Guy De Maupassant. I am not overly impressed. He does capture individual personalities and peccadilloes accurately and the description of scenes and times is very good; but I thought the stories were too long by half and just not worth the effort. I suppose they were considered racy or ribald for the time, but not so much anymore. Most of them I found to be predictable and forgettable. I am glad I have read them. I have had this book for 30 years or so and now I can say that I have read De Maupassant but I won't likely venture there again. </span>
